creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 124 by Various.
Read in English by volunteer readers.

This is a collection of poems read by LibriVox volunteers for October 2013. This collection includes the following:
Among the Rice Fields by Laurence Hope Anecdote of the Jar by Wallace Stevens
Arizona by John Gould Fletcher
Autumn by Siegfried Sassoon
Brotherhood by Edwin Markham
Comic Insects by Rev. Francis Andrew Spilsbury Reid
Consecration by Emily Dickinson
Dawn by William Carlos Williams
Despondency by Louisa May Alcott
The Farmer's Bride by Charlotte Mew
For the Fallen by Robert Laurence Binyon
God Is Our Guide by George Loveless
I Many Times Thought Peace Had Come by Emily Dickinson
If by Rudyard Kipling
I'm Nobody! Who are You? by Emily Dickinson
Joe Hill's Last Will by Joe Hill
Narcissus by James Elroy Flecker
October by Robert Frost
Our House by Christopher Morley
Reluctance by Robert Frost
Roundel by H. L. Mencken
The Twins by Henry Sambrooke Leigh
Verse by Taj Mahomed by Laurence Hope
When the Frost is on the Punkin by James Whitcomb Riley
When the Year Grows Old by Edna St. Vincent Millay
Where the Mind Is Without Fear by Rabindranath Tagore
Worth While by Laurence Hope
In Flanders Fields by John McCrae
We Shall Keep the Faith by Moina Michael

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
